OL,4,CLondon doctors as 32,000 shifts got
OL,5,Cunfilled
OL,7,FResponding to the BMA's claims that
OL,8,Fdoctors in London are offered less for
OL,9,Fextra shifts than elsewhere in the
OL,10,Fcountry, NHS England admitted that
OL,11,F"there will be variation" in pay
OL,12,Facross the health service, as pay
OL,13,Frates for non-contractual work are
OL,14,Fmanaged locally.
OL,16,FIt added: "The NHS has a duty to get
OL,17,Fthe best value for taxpayers' money `
OL,18,FNHS trusts in London have a set of
OL,19,Frate caps that they have agreed to try
OL,20,Fto operate within."
